HEADWORD: Wase
<hw>Wase</hw> <pr>(w⟦amac⟧s)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. Sw.
<ets>vase</ets> a sheaf.]</ety> <def>A bundle of straw, or other
material, to relieve the pressure of burdens carried upon the
head.</def> <mark>[Prov. Eng.]</mark> <rj><au>Halliwell.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
